Interface OWLFacetRestriction

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
OWLFacetRestrictionImpl
public interface OWLFacetRestriction
extends OWLObject

Author: Matthew Horridge
The University Of Manchester
Bio-Health Informatics Group
Date: 11-Jan-2007

A facet restriction is used to restrict a particular datatype. For example the set of integers greater than 18 can be obtained by restricting the integer datatype using a minExclusive facet with a value of 18
